1
00:00:21,530 --> 00:00:24,410
WE'VE BECOME BORED
WITH WATCHING ACTORS

2
00:00:24,950 --> 00:00:27,040
GIVE US PHONY EMOTIONS.

3
00:00:27,240 --> 00:00:29,160
WE'RE TIRED
OF PYROTECHNICS

4
00:00:29,370 --> 00:00:31,210
AND SPECIAL EFFECTS.

5
00:00:31,410 --> 00:00:33,420
WHILE THE WORLD
HE INHABITS...

6
00:00:33,630 --> 00:00:36,420
IS, IN SOME RESPECTS,
COUNTERFEIT,

7
00:00:37,090 --> 00:00:40,010
THERE'S NOTHING FAKE
ABOUT TRUMAN HIMSELF--

8
00:00:41,260 --> 00:00:42,430
NO SCRIPTS,

9
00:00:42,630 --> 00:00:43,760
NO CUE CARDS.

10
00:00:43,970 --> 00:00:46,970
IT ISN'T ALWAYS SHAKESPEARE,
BUT IT'S GENUINE.

11
00:00:48,560 --> 00:00:50,930
IT'S A LIFE.

12
00:00:53,480 --> 00:00:55,730
I'M NOT GOING TO MAKE IT.

13
00:00:55,940 --> 00:00:58,820
YOU'RE GOING TO HAVE
TO GO ON WITHOUT ME.

14
00:01:03,950 --> 00:01:05,660
NO WAY, MISTER.

15
00:01:05,870 --> 00:01:08,410
YOU'RE GOING TO THE TOP
OF THIS MOUNTAIN,

16
00:01:08,620 --> 00:01:11,120
BROKEN LEGS AND ALL.

17
00:01:14,080 --> 00:01:16,080
WE FIND MANY VIEWERS
LEAVE HIM ON

18
00:01:16,290 --> 00:01:18,800
ALL NIGHT FOR COMFORT.

19
00:01:19,670 --> 00:01:22,380
YOU'RE CRAZY,
YOU KNOW THAT?

20
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:26,430
WELL, FOR ME,
THERE IS NO DIFFERENCE

21
00:01:26,640 --> 00:01:28,510
BETWEEN A PRIVATE LIFE
AND A PUBLIC LIFE.

22
00:01:28,720 --> 00:01:31,810
MY LIFE...IS MY LIFE,
IS  THE TRUMAN SHOW.

23
00:01:31,980 --> 00:01:35,100
THE TRUMAN SHOW
IS...   A LIFESTYLE.

24
00:01:35,400 --> 00:01:36,730
IT'S A NOBLE LIFE.

25
00:01:36,940 --> 00:01:39,230
IT IS...

26
00:01:40,530 --> 00:01:41,230
A TRULY BLESSED LIFE.

27
00:01:41,440 --> 00:01:44,650
YEAH, TELL ME SOMETHING
I  DON'T   KNOW.

28
00:01:45,700 --> 00:01:48,580
ALL RIGHT. PROMISE ME
ONE THING, THOUGH.

29
00:01:49,660 --> 00:01:52,500
IF I DIE BEFORE I REACH
THE SUMMIT,

30
00:01:52,700 --> 00:01:55,710
YOU'LL USE ME AS
AN ALTERNATIVE SOURCE OF FOOD.

31
00:01:56,540 --> 00:01:58,880
EW. GROSS.

32
00:02:01,250 --> 00:02:03,720
IT'S ALL TRUE.
IT'S ALL REAL.

33
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:04,420
NOTHING HERE IS FAKE.

34
00:02:04,630 --> 00:02:07,510
NOTHING YOU SEE
ON THIS SHOW IS FAKE.

35
00:02:07,720 --> 00:02:10,260
IT'S MERELY CONTROLLED.

36
00:02:17,270 --> 00:02:19,690
EAT ME, DAMN IT.

37
00:02:19,690 --> 00:02:22,110
THAT'S AN ORDER.

38
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:26,070
MAYBE JUST
YOUR LOVE HANDLES.

39
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:28,240
I HAVE LOVE HANDLES?

40
00:02:28,450 --> 00:02:29,410
YEAH.

41
00:02:29,620 --> 00:02:30,410
LITTLE ONES.

42
00:02:30,620 --> 00:02:31,280
Meryl: TRUMAN!

43
00:02:31,490 --> 00:02:33,700
YOU'RE GOING
TO BE LATE.

44
00:02:33,910 --> 00:02:36,120
OK!

45
00:02:37,620 --> 00:02:39,920
[SIGHS]

46
00:02:44,920 --> 00:02:47,380
[BIRDS TWITTER]

47
00:02:49,390 --> 00:02:50,050
GOOD MORNING.

48
00:02:50,260 --> 00:02:51,600
MORNING.
MORNING.

49
00:02:51,810 --> 00:02:53,470
OH, AND IN CASE
I DON'T SEE YOU,

50
00:02:53,680 --> 00:02:54,890
GOOD AFTERNOON,
GOOD EVENING,

51
00:02:55,100 --> 00:02:56,230
AND GOOD NIGHT.

52
00:02:56,440 --> 00:02:57,440
[ALL LAUGH]

53
00:02:57,640 --> 00:02:58,690
Truman: YEP, YEP.

54
00:02:58,900 --> 00:03:00,270
MORNING.
MORNING, SPENCER.

55
00:03:00,480 --> 00:03:01,400
[BARKS]
HEY, PLUTO.

56
00:03:01,610 --> 00:03:02,690
NO, NO, NO.
GET DOWN.

57
00:03:02,900 --> 00:03:03,730
Spencer:
HE WON'T HURT YOU.

58
00:03:03,940 --> 00:03:06,570
GET DOWN.
HA HA. I KNOW.

59
00:03:06,700 --> 00:03:07,530
IT'S JUST ME.

60
00:03:07,740 --> 00:03:09,870
COME ON, PLUTO.

61
00:03:10,070 --> 00:03:11,070
[BARKS]

62
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:13,540
OHH!

63
00:03:20,830 --> 00:03:23,170
HOLY COW.

64
00:03:31,300 --> 00:03:33,680
WHAT IS IT?

65
00:03:52,990 --> 00:03:54,490
Radio: HERE'S
A NEWS FLASH JUST IN.

66
00:03:54,700 --> 00:03:57,040
AN AIRCRAFT IN TROUBLE
BEGAN SHEDDING PARTS

67
00:03:57,250 --> 00:04:00,250
AS IT FLEW OVER SEAHAVEN
JUST A FEW MOMENTS AGO.

68
00:04:00,250 --> 00:04:00,620
I KNOW.

69
00:04:00,830 --> 00:04:02,290
WOW. LUCKILY,
NO ONE WAS HURT.

70
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:04,170
BUT, HEY,
HOW DO YOU FEEL TODAY?

71
00:04:04,380 --> 00:04:05,000
MMM, MMM.

72
00:04:05,210 --> 00:04:05,710
HEH HEH. THAT'S GOOD.

73
00:04:05,920 --> 00:04:07,130
YOU THINKING OF
FLYING SOMEWHERE?

74
00:04:07,340 --> 00:04:09,010
NOPE.
NO? GOOD.

75
00:04:09,220 --> 00:04:10,340
THIS IS CLASSICAL CLIVE
WITH CLASSICAL DRIVE,

76
00:04:10,550 --> 00:04:13,180
SO WHY DON'T YOU FORGET
ABOUT THE PERILS OF FLYING,

77
00:04:13,390 --> 00:04:16,350
SETTLE BACK, AND LET
THIS MUSIC CALM YOU DOWN?

78
00:04:16,470 --> 00:04:19,180
[CLASSICAL
PIANO MUSIC PLAYS]

79
00:04:21,100 --> 00:04:22,520
DOG FANCY,  PLEASE.

80
00:04:22,730 --> 00:04:23,940
DOG FANCY.

81
00:04:24,150 --> 00:04:25,650
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

82
00:04:25,860 --> 00:04:26,530
Truman: AHH!

83
00:04:26,730 --> 00:04:28,490
GIVE ME A PAPER THERE,
WILL YOU, EARL?

84
00:04:28,690 --> 00:04:29,950
OH, AND, UH...

85
00:04:30,150 --> 00:04:32,820
ONE OF THESE
FOR THE WIFE.

86
00:04:33,070 --> 00:04:34,410
LOVES
HER FASHION MAGS.

87
00:04:34,620 --> 00:04:35,450
WILL THAT BE ALL
FOR YOU, TRUMAN?

88
00:04:35,660 --> 00:04:37,410
THAT'S THE WHOLE
KIT AND CABOODLE.

89
00:04:37,620 --> 00:04:39,620
CATCH YOU LATER.
OK.

90
00:04:39,830 --> 00:04:42,040
YEP.

91
00:04:47,590 --> 00:04:48,590
Man: GOOD MORNING.

92
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:49,760
HEY.

93
00:04:49,970 --> 00:04:50,590
HANK.

94
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:52,260
MORNING, TRUMAN.

95
00:04:52,470 --> 00:04:53,970
Both:
GOOD MORNING, TRUMAN.

96
00:04:54,180 --> 00:04:55,010
HEY, HOW ARE YOU, GUYS?

97
00:04:55,220 --> 00:04:56,300
BEAUTIFUL DAY,
ISN'T IT?

98
00:04:56,510 --> 00:04:57,010
OH. ALWAYS.

99
00:04:57,220 --> 00:05:00,020
OH, AND HOW'S
YOUR LOVELY WIFE?

100
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:01,690
GOOD, GOOD.
HOW ABOUT YOURS?

101
00:05:01,890 --> 00:05:03,310
OH, COULDN'T BE BETTER.

102
00:05:03,520 --> 00:05:04,350
FINE, FINE, FINE.

103
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:06,730
UM, NICE TALKING
TO YOU, TRUMAN.

104
00:05:06,940 --> 00:05:07,690
YOU, TOO.
WE MUST GO NOW.

105
00:05:07,900 --> 00:05:09,230
HEY, THINK ABOUT
THAT POLICY, HUH?

106
00:05:09,440 --> 00:05:12,030
OK, THAT'S 2 FOR 1.
THAT'S A GOOD DEAL.

107
00:05:12,240 --> 00:05:13,160
DOPPELGANGER SPECIAL.

108
00:05:13,360 --> 00:05:14,160
Twins: RIGHT.

109
00:05:14,360 --> 00:05:16,740
HEY.
HI.

110
00:05:17,870 --> 00:05:19,740
HEY, FELLAS.
YOU GOING IN?

111
00:05:19,950 --> 00:05:21,660
GO AHEAD.

112
00:05:21,870 --> 00:05:22,540
HEY.
GO AHEAD.

113
00:05:22,750 --> 00:05:23,960
NO, YOU FIRST,
PLEASE.

114
00:05:24,170 --> 00:05:26,960
I'M NOT THAT ANXIOUS
TO GET THERE.

115
00:05:27,090 --> 00:05:29,340
OHH...

116
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:32,300
[WORKERS CHATTER,
TELEPHONES RING]

117
00:05:41,390 --> 00:05:41,930
[SOFTLY]
YES, HELLO.

118
00:05:42,140 --> 00:05:45,190
COULD I HAVE DIRECTORY
ASSISTANCE FOR FIJI, PLEASE?

119
00:05:45,810 --> 00:05:46,350
FIJI ISLANDS.

120
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:48,940
TRUMAN,
DID YOU SEE THIS?

121
00:05:49,150 --> 00:05:49,610
HA!

122
00:05:49,820 --> 00:05:50,900
UH, I'M SORRY, MA'AM.

123
00:05:51,110 --> 00:05:54,110
IF--IF HE'S IN A COMA,
HE'S PROBABLY UNINSURABLE.

124
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:57,120
[SOFTLY]
HELLO?

125
00:05:57,320 --> 00:05:58,530
YES. UH, FIJI, PLEASE.

126
00:05:58,740 --> 00:06:01,700
DO YOU HAVE A LISTING
FOR LAUREN GARLAND?

127
00:06:03,710 --> 00:06:06,120
NOTHING LISTED?

128
00:06:06,210 --> 00:06:06,540
OK.

129
00:06:06,750 --> 00:06:09,090
DO YOU HAVE
A SYLVIA GARLAND?

130
00:06:09,290 --> 00:06:11,760
"S" FOR SYLVIA.

131
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:15,220
NOTHING?

132
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:18,100
OK. THANK YOU.

133
00:06:40,830 --> 00:06:43,120
[COUGHS]

134
00:06:43,830 --> 00:06:46,120
[COUGHS]

135
00:06:52,550 --> 00:06:53,670
LAWRENCE.
HEY, BURBANK.

136
00:06:53,880 --> 00:06:56,590
GOT A PROSPECT
IN WELLS PARK

137
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:59,180
I NEED YOU TO CLOSE.

138
00:07:00,390 --> 00:07:02,350
W-WELLS PARK?

139
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:03,930
ON, UH...

140
00:07:04,140 --> 00:07:05,350
HARBOR ISLAND?

141
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:07,390
YOU KNOW ANOTHER ONE?

142
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:08,940
WELL, I CAN'T DO IT.

143
00:07:09,150 --> 00:07:10,810
I, UH, HAVE
AN APPOINTMENT.

144
00:07:11,020 --> 00:07:13,150
DENTIST. OR...
YEAH.

145
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:15,030
YOU'RE GOING TO LOSE
A LOT MORE THAN YOUR TEETH

146
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:17,570
IF YOU DON'T MEET
YOUR QUOTA.

147
00:07:17,780 --> 00:07:18,160
LOOK, TRUMAN...

148
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:21,410
THEY'RE MAKING CUTBACKS
AT THE END OF THIS MONTH.

149
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:22,700
CUTBACKS?

150
00:07:22,910 --> 00:07:25,040
YEAH.
NOW, YOU NEED THIS.

151
00:07:25,250 --> 00:07:26,830
BESIDES, A HALF HOUR
ACROSS THE BAY,

152
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:28,540
A LITTLE SEA AIR...

153
00:07:28,750 --> 00:07:31,210
WOULD DO YOU GOOD.

154
00:07:31,250 --> 00:07:31,960
HEY, THANKS.

155
00:07:32,170 --> 00:07:34,670
[SNAPS FINGERS]

156
00:07:42,220 --> 00:07:43,140
HELLO.

157
00:07:43,350 --> 00:07:44,260
FERRY STILL HERE, HUH?

158
00:07:44,470 --> 00:07:46,770
THOUGHT I MIGHT HAVE
MISSED IT.

159
00:07:46,980 --> 00:07:49,440
ONE-WAY OR RETURN?

160
00:07:49,640 --> 00:07:51,940
RETURN.

161
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:54,730
THERE YOU GO, SIR.

162
00:07:54,940 --> 00:07:57,240
HEH HEH.

163
00:07:58,400 --> 00:08:01,110
[SHUTTERS OPEN
ELECTRONICALLY]

164
00:08:10,420 --> 00:08:12,710
[SIGHS]

165
00:08:34,900 --> 00:08:37,190
[SHUDDERS]

166
00:08:48,830 --> 00:08:51,120
UHH...

167
00:08:52,290 --> 00:08:53,790
DO YOU NEED
ANY HELP, SIR?

168
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:56,750
YOU GO AHEAD.
I'LL--I'LL BE FINE.

169
00:08:57,920 --> 00:09:00,260
HEH. YEAH.

170
00:09:11,980 --> 00:09:14,310
HI, HONEY.

171
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:17,690
LOOK WHAT I GOT FREE
AT THE CHECKOUT.

172
00:09:17,900 --> 00:09:19,860
IT'S A CHEF'S PAL.

173
00:09:20,070 --> 00:09:22,400
IT'S A DICER, GRATER,
PEELER--ALL IN ONE.

174
00:09:22,610 --> 00:09:25,530
NEVER NEEDS SHARPENING,
DISHWASHER SAFE.

175
00:09:25,870 --> 00:09:28,120
WOW.

176
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:30,540
THAT'S AMAZING.

177
00:09:31,040 --> 00:09:33,040
Meryl: TRUMAN...

178
00:09:33,250 --> 00:09:35,710
YOU MISSED A SPOT.

179
00:09:37,290 --> 00:09:38,800
OH, JESUS.

180
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:41,340
[LAWN MOWER]

181
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:48,810
MMM.

182
00:09:49,010 --> 00:09:51,560
THAT  IS A BEER.

183
00:09:52,980 --> 00:09:55,690
YOU KNOW, I'M THINKING
ABOUT GETTING OUT, MARLON.

184
00:09:55,900 --> 00:09:56,690
YEAH?

185
00:09:56,900 --> 00:09:57,980
OUT OF WHAT?

186
00:09:58,190 --> 00:09:59,110
OUT OF MY JOB,

187
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:00,780
OUT OF SEAHAVEN.

188
00:10:00,980 --> 00:10:02,070
OFF THIS ISLAND. OUT.

189
00:10:02,280 --> 00:10:02,650
OUT OF YOUR JOB?

190
00:10:02,900 --> 00:10:04,110
WHAT THE HELL'S WRONG
WITH YOUR JOB?

191
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:06,110
YOU HAVE A GREAT JOB,
TRUMAN.

192
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:08,160
YOU HAVE A DESK JOB.

193
00:10:08,370 --> 00:10:10,910
I'D KILL FOR A DESK JOB.

194
00:10:13,500 --> 00:10:13,790
HERE YOU GO.

195
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:16,210
YOU SHOULD TRY STOCKING
VENDING MACHINES FOR A LIVING.

196
00:10:16,420 --> 00:10:17,000
NO, THANKS.

197
00:10:17,210 --> 00:10:18,210
NOW, THERE'S EXCITEMENT.

198
00:10:18,420 --> 00:10:19,460
[BOTH LAUGH]

199
00:10:19,670 --> 00:10:20,960
DON'T YOU EVER
GET ANTSY?

200
00:10:21,170 --> 00:10:23,550
ITCHY FEET?

201
00:10:24,260 --> 00:10:26,720
WHERE'S THERE TO GO?

202
00:10:27,640 --> 00:10:28,390
FIJI.

203
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:29,970
[LAUGHS]

204
00:10:30,180 --> 00:10:31,310
WHERE THE HELL'S FIJI?

205
00:10:31,520 --> 00:10:33,930
NEAR FLORIDA?

206
00:10:35,520 --> 00:10:37,730
HMM.

207
00:10:38,230 --> 00:10:39,060
SEE HERE?

208
00:10:39,270 --> 00:10:39,940
YEAH.

209
00:10:40,150 --> 00:10:42,530
THIS IS US...

210
00:10:42,980 --> 00:10:45,700
AND ALL THE WAY
AROUND HERE...

211
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:47,490
FIJI.

212
00:10:47,700 --> 00:10:49,030
YOU CAN'T GET
ANY FURTHER AWAY

213
00:10:49,240 --> 00:10:51,540
BEFORE YOU START
COMING BACK.

214
00:10:51,740 --> 00:10:54,290
YOU KNOW, THERE ARE
STILL ISLANDS IN FIJI

215
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:56,790
WHERE NO HUMAN BEING
HAS EVER SET FOOT.

216
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:59,250
WHOO.

217
00:11:00,130 --> 00:11:02,840
SO, WHEN ARE YOU
GOING TO GO?

218
00:11:05,090 --> 00:11:07,590
IT'S NOT THAT SIMPLE.

219
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:09,300
IT TAKES...

220
00:11:09,510 --> 00:11:10,850
MONEY,

221
00:11:11,050 --> 00:11:12,140
PLANNING.

222
00:11:12,350 --> 00:11:14,890
I CAN'T JUST UP AND GO.

223
00:11:15,770 --> 00:11:17,060
RIGHT.

224
00:11:17,270 --> 00:11:18,100
I'M GOING TO DO IT.

225
00:11:18,310 --> 00:11:20,360
DON'T WORRY ABOUT THAT.

226
00:11:20,560 --> 00:11:23,400
BONUS TIME IS JUST
AROUND THE CORNER.

227
00:11:25,240 --> 00:11:27,490
HMM.

228
00:11:28,030 --> 00:11:29,910
HEY, YOU COMING
FOR A DRINK?

229
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:32,620
NO. I CAN'T TONIGHT.

230
00:11:50,680 --> 00:11:52,720
I DON'T LIKE THE LOOK
OF THAT WEATHER, SON.

231
00:11:52,930 --> 00:11:53,930
I THINK WE SHOULD
HEAD BACK.

232
00:11:54,140 --> 00:11:55,270
OH, NO, DAD.
NOT YET.

233
00:11:55,470 --> 00:11:56,560
NO, COME ON.
WE SHOULD GO BACK.

234
00:11:56,770 --> 00:11:58,520
A BIT FARTHER.
LISTEN--

235
00:11:58,730 --> 00:11:59,600
PLEASE?

236
00:11:59,810 --> 00:12:01,150
OK.

237
00:12:01,350 --> 00:12:02,610
YES.

238
00:12:02,860 --> 00:12:04,020
[THUNDER]

239
00:12:04,230 --> 00:12:06,490
DADDY!

240
00:12:39,680 --> 00:12:42,020
[THUNDER]

241
00:12:44,360 --> 00:12:46,570
OHH!

242
00:13:03,250 --> 00:13:04,960
HA HA HA HA HA HA!

243
00:13:05,170 --> 00:13:06,380
OH

244
00:13:06,590 --> 00:13:08,920
[THUNDER]

245
00:13:19,930 --> 00:13:22,770
YOU'RE SOAKED.
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

246
00:13:23,020 --> 00:13:25,190
I FIGURE IF WE CAN
SCRAPE TOGETHER 8,000--

247
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:26,770
EVERY TIME YOU AND MARLON
GET TOGETHER--

248
00:13:26,980 --> 00:13:29,190
WE CAN BUM AROUND THE WORLD
FOR A YEAR ON THAT.

249
00:13:29,400 --> 00:13:30,150
AND THEN WHAT, TRUMAN?

250
00:13:30,360 --> 00:13:32,570
WE'D BE WHERE WE WERE
5 YEARS AGO.

251
00:13:32,820 --> 00:13:35,570
YOU'RE TALKING
LIKE A TEENAGER.

252
00:13:35,910 --> 00:13:37,490
WELL, MAYBE I FEEL
LIKE A TEENAGER.

253
00:13:37,700 --> 00:13:40,500
WE HAVE MORTGAGE PAYMENTS,
TRUMAN.

254
00:13:41,250 --> 00:13:42,160
WE HAVE CAR PAYMENTS.

255
00:13:42,370 --> 00:13:43,330
WHAT, WE'RE JUST GOING
TO WALK AWAY

256
00:13:43,540 --> 00:13:44,790
FROM OUR FINANCIAL
