JUST TELL ME
WHAT'S HAPPENING.

575
00:33:59,880 --> 00:34:01,550
GOT TO GO, SIR.
WE'RE REMODELING.

576
00:34:01,760 --> 00:34:02,180
NO, YOU'RE NOT.

577
00:34:02,380 --> 00:34:03,840
WHAT ARE THOSE PEOPLE
DOING BACK THERE?

578
00:34:04,050 --> 00:34:04,680
IT'S NONE OF
YOUR BUSINESS.

579
00:34:04,890 --> 00:34:07,510
IF YOU DON'T TELL ME WHAT'S
HAPPENING, I'LL REPORT YOU!

580
00:34:07,720 --> 00:34:10,180
YOU'RE TRESPASSING.

581
00:34:10,890 --> 00:34:13,190
RIGHT.

582
00:34:41,210 --> 00:34:42,880
MARLON!

583
00:34:43,090 --> 00:34:43,630
TRUMAN.

584
00:34:43,840 --> 00:34:44,510
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

585
00:34:44,720 --> 00:34:45,640
[WHISPERING]
I gotta talk to you.

586
00:34:45,840 --> 00:34:47,100
IT'S A BAD TIME, OK?
I'M WAY BEHIND.

587
00:34:47,300 --> 00:34:50,220
I'M ONTO SOMETHING, MARLON.
SOMETHING BIG.

588
00:34:50,680 --> 00:34:51,480
YOU OK?
YOU LOOK LIKE SHIT.

589
00:34:51,680 --> 00:34:53,600
I THINK I'M MIXED UP
IN SOMETHING.

590
00:34:53,810 --> 00:34:54,190
MIXED UP IN WHAT?

591
00:34:54,390 --> 00:34:55,310
THERE'S NO POINT
TRYING TO EXPLAIN IT,

592
00:34:55,520 --> 00:34:58,520
BUT A LOT OF STRANGE THINGS
HAVE BEEN HAPPENING.

593
00:34:58,520 --> 00:35:00,860
[STAMMERING]

594
00:35:02,740 --> 00:35:04,740
THE PEOPLE ON THE ELEVATOR.

595
00:35:04,950 --> 00:35:06,320
THERE WAS
NO BACKING ON IT.

596
00:35:06,530 --> 00:35:08,370
I LOOKED OUT.
THERE WAS PEOPLE THERE.

597
00:35:08,580 --> 00:35:10,830
AND ON THE RADIO
ON THE WAY TO WORK,

598
00:35:11,040 --> 00:35:12,200
IT STARTS
FOLLOWING ME ALONG,

599
00:35:12,410 --> 00:35:14,250
TALKING ABOUT EVERYTHING
THAT I'M DOING.

600
00:35:14,460 --> 00:35:14,920
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

601
00:35:15,120 --> 00:35:17,210
TRUMAN, LOOK, THIS IS
ONE OF YOUR FANTASIES.

602
00:35:17,420 --> 00:35:18,840
I THINK
THIS IS ABOUT MY DAD.

603
00:35:19,040 --> 00:35:20,000
YOUR DAD?

604
00:35:20,210 --> 00:35:21,000
I THINK HE'S ALIVE.

605
00:35:21,210 --> 00:35:23,670
YEAH. I'LL TELL YOU
ABOUT IT LATER.

606
00:35:23,880 --> 00:35:25,590
I'm definitely
being followed.

607
00:35:25,800 --> 00:35:28,010
WHO?

608
00:35:28,640 --> 00:35:29,850
IT'S HARD TO TELL.

609
00:35:30,060 --> 00:35:32,930
THEY LOOK JUST LIKE
REGULAR PEOPLE.

610
00:35:36,100 --> 00:35:36,940
HOW ABOUT THOSE TWO?

611
00:35:37,150 --> 00:35:38,690
Truman: I DON'T KNOW.

612
00:35:38,900 --> 00:35:39,190
COULD BE.

613
00:35:39,400 --> 00:35:42,440
It's when I'm unpredictable,
that's--they can't...

614
00:35:45,610 --> 00:35:46,910
Did anything happen?

615
00:35:47,110 --> 00:35:47,360
NO.

616
00:35:47,570 --> 00:35:49,660
Mm-hmm. We gotta
get out of here.

617
00:35:49,870 --> 00:35:50,330
You ready to go?

618
00:35:50,530 --> 00:35:51,870
No. I just
came here. Come on.

619
00:35:52,080 --> 00:35:53,080
I TOLD YOU I CAN'T.

620
00:35:53,290 --> 00:35:55,580
[GROWLS]

621
00:35:57,370 --> 00:36:00,250
YOU'RE GONNA GET BOTH OUR ASSES
FIRED. YOU KNOW THAT.

622
00:36:00,460 --> 00:36:02,000
OK, MAN,
LET'S DO IT.

623
00:36:02,210 --> 00:36:03,710
WHAT?
WHATEVER YOU SAY.

624
00:36:03,920 --> 00:36:04,710
I'M GAME.

625
00:36:04,920 --> 00:36:05,720
Marlon: WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

626
00:36:05,920 --> 00:36:08,970
YES, SIREE. YOUR BIRTHDAY
COMES BUT ONCE A YEAR.

627
00:36:11,930 --> 00:36:14,680
Truman: MAYBE I'M BEING
SET UP FOR SOMETHING.

628
00:36:14,890 --> 00:36:17,690
YOU EVER THINK
ABOUT THAT, MARLON?

629
00:36:17,730 --> 00:36:18,600
LIKE YOUR WHOLE LIFE

630
00:36:18,810 --> 00:36:21,230
HAS BEEN BUILDING
TOWARDS SOMETHING?

631
00:36:21,440 --> 00:36:22,730
MMM, NO.

632
00:36:22,940 --> 00:36:24,530
WHEN YOU WERE
HAULING CHICKENS

633
00:36:24,730 --> 00:36:26,570
IN THE SUMMER
FOR KAISER,

634
00:36:26,780 --> 00:36:27,990
WHAT WAS
THE FURTHEST

635
00:36:28,200 --> 00:36:30,280
YOU EVER GOT
OFF THE ISLAND?

636
00:36:30,490 --> 00:36:31,620
WENT ALL OVER.

637
00:36:31,870 --> 00:36:34,740
NEVER FOUND A PLACE
LIKE THIS, THOUGH.

638
00:36:35,000 --> 00:36:36,620
LOOK AT THAT SUNSET,
TRUMAN.

639
00:36:36,830 --> 00:36:38,670
IT'S PERFECT.

640
00:36:38,870 --> 00:36:40,710
YEAH.

641
00:36:40,920 --> 00:36:43,090
THAT'S THE BIG GUY.

642
00:36:43,300 --> 00:36:45,590
QUITE A PAINTBRUSH
HE'S GOT.

643
00:36:45,800 --> 00:36:48,050
YUP.

644
00:36:50,090 --> 00:36:52,890
JUST BETWEEN YOU
AND ME, MARLON...

645
00:36:54,220 --> 00:36:56,890
I'M GOING AWAY
FOR A WHILE.

646
00:36:57,480 --> 00:36:59,390
REALLY?

647
00:36:59,600 --> 00:37:00,520
YEAH.

648
00:37:00,730 --> 00:37:03,400
Mother: OH, LITTLE ANGEL.

649
00:37:03,940 --> 00:37:06,360
[WOMEN LAUGH]

650
00:37:09,030 --> 00:37:11,490
OH, MY LITTLE CLOWN.

651
00:37:14,120 --> 00:37:15,450
OLD CARROT TOP.

652
00:37:15,660 --> 00:37:18,080
THE BEST PHOTOS.

653
00:37:19,540 --> 00:37:20,250
OHH.
OHH.

654
00:37:20,460 --> 00:37:22,000
WE SHOULD BE GETTING YOU
HOME, MOTHER.

655
00:37:22,210 --> 00:37:25,170
HOLD ON A MINUTE.
HERE'S US AT MOUNT RUSHMORE.

656
00:37:25,300 --> 00:37:27,800
DO YOU REMEMBER, TRUMAN,
WHEN DAD WAS STILL WITH US?

657
00:37:28,010 --> 00:37:29,470
THAT WAS QUITE A DRIVE.

658
00:37:29,670 --> 00:37:32,430
YOU SLEPT
THE WHOLE WAY THERE.

659
00:37:32,430 --> 00:37:33,470
Truman:
IT LOOKS SO SMALL.

660
00:37:33,680 --> 00:37:36,220
THINGS ALWAYS DO
WHEN YOU LOOK BACK, DARLING.

661
00:37:36,430 --> 00:37:37,060
OH, LOOK, TRUMAN.

662
00:37:37,270 --> 00:37:39,980
THE HAPPIEST DAY
OF OUR LIVES.

663
00:37:42,020 --> 00:37:43,110
OH, LOOK.

664
00:37:43,310 --> 00:37:45,230
JEAN, JODIE, JOANNE.

665
00:37:45,440 --> 00:37:47,070
DOESN'T SHE LOOK
BEAUTIFUL, TRUMAN?

666
00:37:47,280 --> 00:37:48,990
WELL, SHE STILL DOES.

667
00:37:49,190 --> 00:37:52,280
AND THERE'S LOTS OF PAGES
LEFT OVER FOR BABY PHOTOS.

668
00:37:53,450 --> 00:37:56,410
I WOULD LIKE TO HOLD
A GRANDCHILD IN MY ARMS

669
00:37:56,700 --> 00:37:57,040
BEFORE I GO.

670
00:37:57,240 --> 00:37:59,580
ANGELA, WE REALLY SHOULD
BE GETTING YOU HOME.

671
00:37:59,790 --> 00:38:00,290
I'LL TAKE HER.

672
00:38:00,500 --> 00:38:02,540
NO, NO, NO.
YOU STAY, RELAX.

673
00:38:02,750 --> 00:38:03,130
ENJOY YOURSELF.

674
00:38:03,330 --> 00:38:05,380
YOUR FAVORITE SHOW
WILL BE COMING ON.

675
00:38:05,590 --> 00:38:08,130
BESIDES, WE HAVE
SOMETHING TO DISCUSS.

676
00:38:08,340 --> 00:38:11,050
A CERTAIN PERSON'S
BIRTHDAY.

677
00:38:11,050 --> 00:38:12,680
OH, I SEE.

678
00:38:12,880 --> 00:38:14,180
TV announcer: AND THERE'LL BE
ANOTHER EPISODE

679
00:38:14,390 --> 00:38:16,100
OF  I LOVE LUCY
