00:43:02,510 --> 00:43:04,890
OH, THAT'S OK.

756
00:43:05,890 --> 00:43:06,340
HOW CAN I HELP?

757
00:43:06,550 --> 00:43:08,640
I WOULD LIKE TO BOOK
A FLIGHT TO FIJI.

758
00:43:08,850 --> 00:43:11,600
WHEN WOULD YOU LIKE
TO LEAVE?

759
00:43:14,390 --> 00:43:16,650
TODAY.

760
00:43:26,950 --> 00:43:28,910
[BEEP]

761
00:43:29,120 --> 00:43:29,990
[BEEP]

762
00:43:30,200 --> 00:43:32,500
[BEEP]

763
00:43:32,580 --> 00:43:33,250
I'M SORRY.

764
00:43:33,460 --> 00:43:36,420
I DON'T HAVE ANYTHING
FOR AT LEAST A MONTH.

765
00:43:37,130 --> 00:43:37,920
A MONTH?

766
00:43:38,130 --> 00:43:40,670
IT'S THE BUSY SEASON.

767
00:43:42,050 --> 00:43:43,470
YOU WANT TO BOOK THE FLIGHT?

768
00:43:43,670 --> 00:43:45,680
IT DOESN'T MATTER.

769
00:43:45,880 --> 00:43:48,680
I'LL MAKE OTHER
ARRANGEMENTS, OK?

770
00:43:51,850 --> 00:43:54,480
Man:
LAST CALL FOR CHICAGO!

771
00:43:55,690 --> 00:43:58,060
ALL ABOARD!

772
00:44:01,270 --> 00:44:03,030
[WHISTLES]

773
00:44:03,240 --> 00:44:05,570
THANK YOU.

774
00:44:07,490 --> 00:44:10,080
WINDY CITY, HERE WE COME.

775
00:44:11,200 --> 00:44:13,580
HI.
HI.

776
00:44:15,370 --> 00:44:16,920
HELLO.

777
00:44:17,120 --> 00:44:19,330
HI.

778
00:44:19,580 --> 00:44:20,540
Truman: SISTERS.

779
00:44:20,750 --> 00:44:23,260
HEY, MOM, ISN'T THAT--

780
00:44:23,760 --> 00:44:26,380
Mom: SHH.
FACE THE FRONT.

781
00:44:34,640 --> 00:44:37,060
[GEARS GRIND]

782
00:44:40,360 --> 00:44:42,730
[GEARS GRIND]

783
00:44:46,360 --> 00:44:48,280
[GEARS GRIND]

784
00:44:48,490 --> 00:44:50,070
[ENGINE STALLS]

785
00:44:50,280 --> 00:44:51,530
[RADIATOR HISSING]

786
00:44:51,740 --> 00:44:54,540
EVERYBODY OFF.
WE'VE GOT A PROBLEM.

787
00:45:14,180 --> 00:45:16,600
I'M SORRY, SON.

788
00:45:29,150 --> 00:45:31,240
HIS FATHER WAS FROM
CHICAGO, WASN'T HE?

789
00:45:31,450 --> 00:45:33,830
NO. HIS DENTIST
WAS FROM PENSACOLA.

790
00:45:34,030 --> 00:45:35,330
HIS FATHER
WAS FROM DES MOINES.

791
00:45:35,540 --> 00:45:37,450
BUT HOW COME HE WANTS
TO GO TO CHICAGO?

792
00:45:37,660 --> 00:45:40,710
HE'S NOT GOING TO CHICAGO.
HE'S NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

793
00:45:40,920 --> 00:45:43,540
HE HAS TO HAVE IT OUT
WITH MERYL.

794
00:45:43,750 --> 00:45:46,170
[PLUTO BARKS]

795
00:45:59,100 --> 00:46:01,390
TRUMAN?

796
00:46:05,270 --> 00:46:07,730
HONEY, ARE YOU OK?

797
00:46:07,980 --> 00:46:10,280
GET IN.

798
00:46:12,490 --> 00:46:14,740
TRUMAN.

799
00:46:15,120 --> 00:46:17,370
LOOK.

800
00:46:20,080 --> 00:46:22,210
WHAT?
SHH.

801
00:46:22,420 --> 00:46:23,000
I PREDICT

802
00:46:23,210 --> 00:46:24,840
THAT IN JUST A MOMENT

803
00:46:25,040 --> 00:46:27,800
WE WILL SEE A LADY
ON A RED BIKE,

804
00:46:28,670 --> 00:46:30,260
FOLLOWED BY A MAN
WITH FLOWERS

805
00:46:30,470 --> 00:46:33,090
AND A VOLKSWAGEN BEETLE

806
00:46:33,390 --> 00:46:34,550
WITH A DENTED FENDER.

807
00:46:34,760 --> 00:46:36,260
TRUMAN, PLEASE.

808
00:46:36,470 --> 00:46:38,890
Truman: LOOK.

809
00:46:42,390 --> 00:46:44,730
LADY...

810
00:46:45,650 --> 00:46:47,980
FLOWERS...

811
00:46:48,070 --> 00:46:50,400
Both: AND...

812
00:46:51,900 --> 00:46:53,610
TRUMAN, THIS IS SILLY.

813
00:46:53,820 --> 00:46:55,120
THERE IT IS!
THERE IT IS!

814
00:46:55,320 --> 00:46:58,200
THERE'S THAT DENTED
BEETLE! YES!

815
00:46:58,540 --> 00:47:00,830
AAAAAAH!

816
00:47:00,870 --> 00:47:03,250
HA HA HA!

817
00:47:04,120 --> 00:47:07,000
DON'T YOU WANT TO KNOW
HOW I DID THAT?

818
00:47:07,040 --> 00:47:07,960
I'LL TELL YOU.

819
00:47:08,170 --> 00:47:08,960
THEY'RE ON A LOOP.

820
00:47:09,170 --> 00:47:10,590
THEY GO AROUND THE BLOCK.

821
00:47:10,800 --> 00:47:11,470
THEY COME BACK.

822
00:47:11,670 --> 00:47:12,720
THEY GO AROUND AGAIN.

823
00:47:12,920 --> 00:47:14,130
THEY JUST GO
ROUND AND ROUND.

824
00:47:14,340 --> 00:47:14,680
ROUND AND ROUND.

825
00:47:14,890 --> 00:47:17,970
I INVITED RITA AND MARLON
FOR A BARBECUE ON SUNDAY.

826
00:47:18,810 --> 00:47:19,350
I WON'T BE HERE
SUNDAY.

827
00:47:19,560 --> 00:47:22,270
AND I NEED YOU TO REMIND ME
THAT WE NEED MORE CHARCOAL.

828
00:47:22,480 --> 00:47:25,400
ARE YOU LISTENING
TO A WORD I'M SAYING?

829
00:47:25,770 --> 00:47:28,730
YOU'RE UPSET BECAUSE
YOU WANT TO GO TO FIJI.

830
00:47:29,650 --> 00:47:31,740
IS THAT IT?

831
00:47:31,940 --> 00:47:34,280
OK, OK, GO.

832
00:47:37,280 --> 00:47:40,160
I THINK YOU SHOULD SAVE
FOR A FEW MONTHS

833
00:47:40,160 --> 00:47:42,660
AND THEN GO. THERE.

834
00:47:42,910 --> 00:47:44,660
ARE YOU HAPPY NOW?

835
00:47:44,870 --> 00:47:47,500
I WANT TO GO TAKE A SHOWER.

836
00:47:48,340 --> 00:47:49,460
LET'S GO NOW.

837
00:47:49,670 --> 00:47:51,130
I'M READY TO GO NOW.
WHY WAIT?

838
00:47:51,340 --> 00:47:52,380
EARLY BIRD
GATHERS NO MOSS.

839
00:47:52,590 --> 00:47:55,470
ROLLING STONE CATCHES
THE WORM, RIGHT?

840
00:47:55,760 --> 00:47:56,800
[LAUGHS]

841
00:47:57,010 --> 00:47:59,810
Meryl: TRUMAN,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

842
00:48:01,010 --> 00:48:03,270
OH!

843
00:48:04,890 --> 00:48:05,890
TRUMAN!

844
00:48:06,100 --> 00:48:08,940
WHERE SHALL WE GO?
WHERE SHALL WE GO?

845
00:48:09,820 --> 00:48:11,320
TRUMAN, WHERE
ARE WE GOING?

846
00:48:11,530 --> 00:48:14,610
I DON'T REALLY KNOW.
I GUESS I'M BEING SPONTANEOUS.

847
00:48:16,030 --> 00:48:17,240
SOMEBODY HELP ME!

848
00:48:17,450 --> 00:48:19,410
I'M BEING SPONTANEOUS!

849
00:48:19,620 --> 00:48:20,700
Meryl: TRUMAN.

850
00:48:20,910 --> 00:48:21,490
FORGET FIJI.

851
00:48:21,700 --> 00:48:23,910
CAN'T VERY WELL DRIVE
TO FIJI, CAN WE?

852
00:48:24,120 --> 00:48:26,370
NO.

853
00:48:26,830 --> 00:48:29,460
WHAT ABOUT
ATLANTIC CITY?

854
00:48:29,630 --> 00:48:31,500
OH, NO, YOU HATE
TO GAMBLE.

855
00:48:31,710 --> 00:48:32,590
THAT'S RIGHT,
I DO, DON'T I?

856
00:48:32,800 --> 00:48:34,420
SO WHY WOULD YOU WANT
TO GO THERE?

857
00:48:34,630 --> 00:48:35,760
BECAUSE I NEVER HAVE.

858
00:48:35,970 --> 00:48:38,840
THAT'S WHY PEOPLE
GO PLACES, ISN'T IT?

859
00:48:39,050 --> 00:48:42,010
TRUMAN, TRUMAN,
I THINK I'M GONNA THROW UP.

860
00:48:42,600 --> 00:48:44,890
ME, TOO.

861
00:48:52,070 --> 00:48:53,820
BLOCKED AT EVERY TURN.

862
00:48:54,030 --> 00:48:56,530
BEAUTIFULLY SYNCHRONIZED,
DON'T YOU AGREE?

863
00:48:56,740 --> 00:48:58,950
YOU'RE BLAMING ME
FOR THE TRAFFIC?

864
00:48:59,160 --> 00:49:01,490
SHOULD I?

865
00:49:07,040 --> 00:49:09,370
TRUMAN...

866
00:49:09,580 --> 00:49:11,500
LET'S GO HOME.

867
00:49:11,710 --> 00:49:12,460
YOU'RE RIGHT.

868
00:49:12,670 --> 00:49:13,960
WE COULD BE STUCK
HERE FOR HOURS.

869
00:49:14,170 --> 00:49:16,920
IT COULD BE LIKE THIS
ALL THE WAY TO ATLANTIC CITY.

870
00:49:17,130 --> 00:49:19,130
LET'S GO BACK.

871
00:49:19,340 --> 00:49:22,260
I'M SORRY. I DON'T KNOW
WHAT GOT INTO ME.

872
00:49:26,100 --> 00:49:28,850
Meryl: CAN YOU
PLEASE SLOW DOWN?

873
00:49:29,190 --> 00:49:31,610
YES, I CAN.

874
00:49:32,560 --> 00:49:34,020
TRUMAN! TRUMAN!
THAT'S OUR TURNOFF!

875
00:49:34,230 --> 00:49:35,320
I CHANGED MY MIND AGAIN.

876
00:49:35,530 --> 00:49:37,400
WHAT'S NEW ORLEANS LIKE
THIS TIME OF YEAR?

877
00:49:37,610 --> 00:49:40,280
MARDI GRAS! WHOO!
HA HA HA!

878
00:49:40,950 --> 00:49:42,660
[HONKING]

879
00:49:42,870 --> 00:49:45,120
WHOO!

880
00:49:45,240 --> 00:49:48,210
LOOK, MERYL, SAME ROAD,
NO CARS. IT'S MAGIC.

881
00:49:51,420 --> 00:49:52,000
HA HA HA!

882
00:49:52,210 --> 00:49:54,460
YOU LET ME OUT. YOU'RE
NOT RIGHT IN THE HEAD.

883
00:49:54,670 --> 00:49:56,840
YOU WANT TO DESTROY
YOURSELF, DO IT ON YOUR OWN.

884
00:49:57,050 --> 00:49:59,840
I THINK I'D LIKE
A LITTLE COMPANY.

885
00:50:06,310 --> 00:50:07,850
OH, TRUMAN...

886
00:50:08,060 --> 00:50:10,690
YOU KNEW
THIS WOULD HAPPEN.

887
00:50:11,190 --> 00:50:14,150
YOU KNOW YOU CAN'T
DRIVE OVER WATER.

888
00:50:14,310 --> 00:50:17,150
LET'S GO HOME
WHERE YOU'LL FEEL SAFE.

889
00:50:19,990 --> 00:50:20,950
GIVE ME YOUR HAND.

890
00:50:21,150 --> 00:50:22,780
SWEETIE--

891
00:50:22,990 --> 00:50:24,780
DRIVE.

892
00:50:24,990 --> 00:50:25,910
TRUMAN!

893
00:50:26,120 --> 00:50:29,250
WE SHOULDN'T BE DOING THIS!
WE'RE BREAKING THE LAW!

894
00:50:29,410 --> 00:50:31,080
OH, MY!
YOU CAN DO IT!

895
00:50:31,290 --> 00:50:32,620
PLEASE, DON'T!

896
00:50:32,830 --> 00:50:34,630
YOU CAN MAKE IT!
TRUMAN!

897
00:50:34,840 --> 00:50:35,920
AAH! OH, WE'RE OVER!

898
00:50:36,130 --> 00:50:39,090
WE'RE OVER THE BRIDGE!
WE'RE OVER THE BRIDGE!

899
00:50:39,130 --> 00:50:39,460
WE'RE OVER?

900
00:50:39,670 --> 00:50:41,760
WE'RE OVER THE BRIDGE.
WE'RE OVER THE BRIDGE.

901
00:50:41,970 --> 00:50:42,720
WE'RE OVER!

902
00:50:42,930 --> 00:50:45,300
HA HA HA HA!

903
00:50:48,100 --> 00:50:50,020
TRUMAN! WHAT
ABOUT THAT SIGN?

904
00:50:50,230 --> 00:50:52,810
THEY'RE EXAGGERATING.
WE'LL BE FINE.

905
00:50:53,020 --> 00:50:55,940
EXAGGERATING?
DO YOU BELIEVE THAT?

906
00:50:56,860 --> 00:50:59,190
[YELLING]

907
00:50:59,230 --> 00:51:02,150
OH, MY! OH, MY!
TRUMAN, WE'RE ON FIRE!

908
00:51:02,360 --> 00:51:03,360
IT'S OK.
WE'RE ON FIRE!

909
00:51:03,570 --> 00:51:05,700
IT'S OK.
IT'S JUST SMOKE.

910
00:51:05,910 --> 00:51:07,280
YOU OK?
YES.

911
00:51:07,490 --> 00:51:09,370
WANT TO DO IT AGAIN?
NO!

912
00:51:09,580 --> 00:51:10,410
HA HA HA HA!

913
00:51:10,620 --> 00:51:13,210
TRUMAN, STOP!
OH, GOD!

914
00:51:14,330 --> 00:51:14,500
OH!

915
00:51:14,710 --> 00:51:16,500
SO, WHAT ARE WE GOING
TO DO FOR MONEY

916
00:51:16,710 --> 00:51:19,300
WHEN WE GET
TO NEW ORLEANS?

917
00:51:19,500 --> 00:51:22,220
I HAVE MY SEAHAVEN
BANK CARD.

918
00:51:22,720 --> 00:51:25,840
WE'RE JUST GOING TO EAT
INTO OUR SAVINGS, IS THAT IT?

919
00:51:27,140 --> 00:51:29,720
I'M GOING TO HAVE TO CALL
YOUR MOTHER WHEN WE GET THERE.

920
00:51:29,930 --> 00:51:31,060
SHE'S GOING
TO BE WORRIED SICK.

921
00:51:31,270 --> 00:51:34,230
I DON'T KNOW HOW
SHE'S GOING TO TAKE THIS.

922
00:51:46,280 --> 00:51:47,620
WHAT NOW?

923
00:51:47,820 --> 00:51:50,790
Loudspeaker: RED ALERT!
THIS IS A RED ALERT!

924
00:51:51,290 --> 00:51:52,540
[PEOPLE YELLING]

925
00:51:52,750 --> 00:51:53,710
[CAR HORNS HONKING]

926
00:51:53,910 --> 00:51:56,540
TRUMAN, IT LOOKS LIKE
A LEAK AT THE PLANT.

927
00:51:56,750 --> 00:51:58,670
BACK UP! BACK UP!
LEAK AT THE PLANT.

928
00:51:58,880 --> 00:52:00,050
WE HAD TO SHUT HER DOWN.

929
00:52:00,250 --> 00:52:01,510
IS THERE
ANY WAY AROUND?

930
00:52:01,710 --> 00:52:02,550
WHOLE AREA'S
BEING EVACUATED.

931
00:52:02,760 --> 00:52:04,050
IS THERE
ANYTHING I CAN DO?

932
00:52:04,260 --> 00:52:04,720
NO, MA'AM.

933
00:52:04,930 --> 00:52:05,720
THANK YOU
FOR YOUR HELP.

934
00:52:05,930 --> 00:52:08,550
YOU'RE WELCOME,
TRUMAN.

935
00:52:09,550 --> 00:52:11,850
TRUMAN.

936
00:52:13,680 --> 00:52:15,600
TRUMAN! TRUMAN!

937
00:52:15,810 --> 00:52:17,810
TRUMAN, COME BACK!

938
00:52:18,020 --> 00:52:20,690
TRUMAN! TRUMAN!
STOP HIM!

939
00:52:21,230 --> 00:52:22,570
UNH!

940
00:52:22,780 --> 00:52:23,490
TRUMAN!

941
00:52:23,690 --> 00:52:25,320
[WHISTLES BLOWING]

942
00:52:25,530 --> 00:52:27,990
HEAD TO THE LEFT!

943
00:52:33,700 --> 00:52:36,000
AAH! AAH!

944
00:52:42,550 --> 00:52:44,880
STAY AWAY!

945
00:52:48,890 --> 00:52:49,890
UNH! AAH!

946
00:52:50,100 --> 00:52:52,390
UNH! NO!

947
00:52:52,760 --> 00:52:54,350
NO!

948
00:52:54,560 --> 00:52:56,180
Radio:
...NOW IN CUSTODY.

949
00:52:56,390 --> 00:52:58,850
[TRUMAN GROANING]

950
00:52:58,940 --> 00:53:01,310
THANK YOU BOTH SO MUCH
FOR YOUR HELP.

951
00:53:01,520 --> 00:53:02,900
I REALLY APPRECIATE IT.

952
00:53:03,110 --> 00:53:04,230
HE'S LUCKY TO BE
ALIVE, MA'AM.

953
00:53:04,440 --> 00:53:06,320
NEXT TIME, WE'LL HAVE
TO FILE CHARGES.

954
00:53:06,530 --> 00:53:07,950
I UNDERSTAND.

955
00:53:08,160 --> 00:53:10,070
THANKS AGAIN.

956
00:53:10,280 --> 00:53:12,660
GOOD NIGHT.

957
00:53:28,840 --> 00:53:31,640
LET ME GET YOU
SOME HELP, TRUMAN.

958
00:53:32,180 --> 00:53:34,600
YOU'RE NOT WELL.

959
00:53:35,970 --> 00:53:38,850
WHY DO YOU WANT
TO HAVE A BABY WITH ME?

960
00:53:40,150 --> 00:53:41,650
YOU CAN'T STAND ME.

961
00:53:41,860 --> 00:53:43,980
THAT'S NOT TRUE.

962
00:53:44,190 --> 00:53:46,490
[SCOFFS]

963
00:53:48,070 --> 00:53:50,780
WHY DON'T YOU LET ME FIX YOU
SOME OF THIS NEW MOCOCOA DRINK?

964
00:53:50,990 --> 00:53:53,280
ALL NATURAL COCOA BEANS
FROM THE UPPER SLOPES

965
00:53:53,490 --> 00:53:55,580
OF MOUNT NICARAGUA.
NO ARTIFICIAL SWEETENERS.

966
00:53:55,790 --> 00:53:58,580
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

967
00:53:59,370 --> 00:54:00,290
WHO ARE YOU TALKING TO?

968
00:54:00,500 --> 00:54:03,500
I'VE TASTED OTHER COCOAS.
THIS IS THE BEST.

969
00:54:04,250 --> 00:54:07,340
WHAT THE HELL DOES THIS
HAVE TO DO WITH ANYTHING?

970
00:54:09,090 --> 00:54:10,430
TELL ME WHAT'S HAPPENING!

971
00:54:10,630 --> 00:54:13,680
YOU'RE HAVING A NERVOUS
BREAKDOWN, THAT'S WHAT.

972
00:54:14,050 --> 00:54:16,810
YOU'RE PART OF THIS,
AREN'T YOU?

973
00:54:19,640 --> 00:54:21,140
TRUMAN!
MERYL!

974
00:54:21,350 --> 00:54:23,900
YOU...ARE...SCARING ME!

975
00:54:24,310 --> 00:54:26,440
NO, YOU'RE SCARING ME, MERYL.

976
00:54:26,650 --> 00:54:29,440
WHAT ARE YOU GOING TO DO?
DICE ME?

977
00:54:30,320 --> 00:54:31,530
SLICE ME
AND PEEL ME?

978
00:54:31,740 --> 00:54:33,410
THERE ARE
SO MANY CHOICES!

979
00:54:33,620 --> 00:54:36,080
AAH! DO SOMETHING!

980
00:54:37,990 --> 00:54:39,290
WHAT?

981
00:54:39,500 --> 00:54:42,040
WHAT DID YOU SAY?
WHO ARE YOU TALKING TO?

982
00:54:42,250 --> 00:54:44,630
NOTHING. I DIDN'T
SAY ANYTHING.

983
00:54:44,840 --> 00:54:46,460
I DIDN'T
SAY ANYTHING.

984
00:54:46,670 --> 00:54:47,880
YOU SAID,
"DO SOMETHING."

985
00:54:48,090 --> 00:54:49,840
NO, I DIDN'T. I WASN'T
TALKING TO ANYBODY.

986
00:54:50,050 --> 00:54:51,170
TALK TO ME!

987
00:54:51,380 --> 00:54:51,720
[BANGING]

988
00:54:51,930 --> 00:54:53,640
I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING!
PLEASE STOP!

989
00:54:53,840 --> 00:54:55,930
STAY WHERE
YOU ARE!

990
00:54:56,140 --> 00:54:58,430
TRUMAN?

991
00:54:59,770 --> 00:55:00,560
TRUMAN?

992
00:55:00,770 --> 00:55:03,480
OH, THANK GOD!
OH, THANK GOD!

993
00:55:05,650 --> 00:55:07,480
[SOBBING]

994
00:55:07,690 --> 00:55:09,730
HOW CAN ANYONE
EXPECT ME

995
00:55:09,940 --> 00:55:12,780
TO CARRY ON UNDER
THESE CONDITIONS?

996
00:55:13,070 --> 00:55:15,280
IT'S UNPROFESSIONAL!

997
00:55:15,490 --> 00:55:17,870
SHH, IT'S OK.

998
00:55:19,700 --> 00:55:21,620
EVERYTHING'S
GONNA BE OK.

999
00:55:21,830 --> 00:55:22,750
OH, GOD!

1000
00:55:22,960 --> 00:55:25,540
IT'S ALL
GONNA BE FINE.

1001
00:55:27,420 --> 00:55:30,260
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
TO THINK, MARLON.

1002
00:55:33,720 --> 00:55:36,470
MAYBE I'M LOSING
MY MIND, BUT...

1003
00:55:39,970 --> 00:55:43,140
IT FEELS LIKE THE WHOLE WORLD
REVOLVES AROUND ME SOMEHOW.

1004
00:55:45,440 --> 00:55:48,360
THAT'S A LOT OF WORLD
FOR ONE MAN, TRUMAN.

1005
00:55:50,480 --> 00:55:53,280
SURE THAT'S NOT
WISHFUL THINKING?

1006
00:55:53,320 --> 00:55:54,910
YOU WISHING YOU'D MADE

1007
00:55:55,110 --> 00:55:57,120
SOMETHING MORE
OUT OF YOURSELF?

1008
00:55:57,320 --> 00:55:59,120
COME ON, WHO HASN'T
SAT IN THE JOHN,

1009
00:55:59,330 --> 00:56:02,580
HAD AN IMAGINARY INTERVIEW
ON  SEAHAVEN TONIGHT?

