GO TO THE CABIN CAM.

1518
01:22:32,710 --> 01:22:35,050
CABIN CAM.

1519
01:22:36,470 --> 01:22:38,130
THERE. PERFECT.

1520
01:22:38,340 --> 01:22:40,890
THAT'S OUR HERO SHOT.

1521
01:23:05,700 --> 01:23:07,500
LET'S GET ANOTHER BOAT
OUT THERE.

1522
01:23:07,700 --> 01:23:10,540
OK. LISTEN, GUS, I NEED YOU TO
TALK TO THE GUYS ON THE FERRY.

1523
01:23:10,750 --> 01:23:13,710
COME ON. GET IT MOVING.
GET IT OUT OF HERE.

1524
01:23:14,090 --> 01:23:16,090
[GRINDING]

1525
01:23:16,300 --> 01:23:17,210
Gus: COME ON.

1526
01:23:17,420 --> 01:23:18,300
I'M JUST A BUS DRIVER.

1527
01:23:18,510 --> 01:23:21,470
BOTTOM LINE IS,
THEY CAN'T DRIVE THE BOAT.

1528
01:23:21,640 --> 01:23:24,050
THEY'RE ACTORS.

1529
01:23:26,640 --> 01:23:29,140
HOW DO WE STOP HIM?

1530
01:23:39,320 --> 01:23:41,660
OK, UH...

1531
01:23:42,280 --> 01:23:45,370
WE'RE GOING TO BE ACCESSING
THE WEATHER PROGRAM NOW.

1532
01:23:46,660 --> 01:23:48,910
SO HOLD ON TO YOUR HATS.

1533
01:23:49,120 --> 01:23:50,410
YOU GOT THAT?

1534
01:23:50,620 --> 01:23:53,710
NO. I THINK WE'RE GONNA
WANT TO LOCALIZE THE STORM

1535
01:23:54,670 --> 01:23:57,050
OVER THE BOAT.

1536
01:23:58,460 --> 01:24:00,050
YOU CAN GET
THE COORDINATES FOR THAT.

1537
01:24:00,300 --> 01:24:03,090
THERE'S NO RESCUE BOAT.
HE WON'T KNOW WHAT TO DO.

1538
01:24:03,300 --> 01:24:06,100
HE'LL TURN BACK.
HE'LL BE TOO AFRAID.

1539
01:24:06,100 --> 01:24:08,430
[WHISPERING]

1540
01:24:08,720 --> 01:24:11,180
THERE SHE BLOWS.

1541
01:24:21,360 --> 01:24:22,490
[MOTOR STALLING]

1542
01:24:22,700 --> 01:24:24,990
COME ON.

1543
01:24:47,180 --> 01:24:48,510
GIVE ME SOME LIGHTNING.

1544
01:24:48,720 --> 01:24:50,060
[THUNDER]

1545
01:24:50,270 --> 01:24:51,680
AGAIN!

1546
01:24:51,890 --> 01:24:54,270
HIT HIM AGAIN!

1547
01:25:04,280 --> 01:25:06,700
FOR GOD'S SAKE, CHRISTOF,
THE WHOLE WORLD IS WATCHING.

1548
01:25:06,910 --> 01:25:08,490
WE CAN'T LET HIM DIE
IN FRONT OF A LIVE AUDIENCE.

1549
01:25:08,700 --> 01:25:11,580
HE WAS BORN IN FRONT
OF A LIVE AUDIENCE.

1550
01:25:39,940 --> 01:25:40,820
[CHEERING]

1551
01:25:41,020 --> 01:25:43,320
TRUMAN!

1552
01:25:45,280 --> 01:25:47,860
YOU CAN DO IT!
HOLD ON!

1553
01:26:12,430 --> 01:26:15,140
IS THAT THE BEST
YOU CAN DO?

1554
01:26:16,020 --> 01:26:18,770
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
TO KILL ME!

1555
01:26:20,020 --> 01:26:22,110
WHAT SHALL WE DO
WITH A DRUNKEN SAILOR

1556
01:26:22,320 --> 01:26:22,860
ON BEHALF OF THE STUDIO,

1557
01:26:23,070 --> 01:26:24,480
I DEMAND THAT YOU
CEASE TRANSMISSION.

1558
01:26:24,690 --> 01:26:25,110
KEEP RUNNING.

1559
01:26:25,320 --> 01:26:27,320
WHAT SHALL WE DO
WITH A DRUNKEN SAILOR

1560
01:26:27,530 --> 01:26:29,660
EARLY IN THE MORNIN'?

1561
01:26:29,870 --> 01:26:31,660
INCREASE THE WIND.

1562
01:26:31,870 --> 01:26:32,490
INCREASE THE WIND!

1563
01:26:32,700 --> 01:26:35,370
[TRUMAN
CONTINUES SINGING]

1564
01:26:35,500 --> 01:26:36,830
I'M TELLING YOU
FOR THE LAST TIME.

1565
01:26:37,040 --> 01:26:38,080
HOW CLOSE IS HE?
VERY.

1566
01:26:38,290 --> 01:26:39,460
CAPSIZE HIM.
TIP HIM OVER.

1567
01:26:39,670 --> 01:26:40,210
DAMN YOU,
CHRISTOF!

1568
01:26:40,420 --> 01:26:42,040
YOU CAN'T. HE'S TIED
HIMSELF TO THE BOAT!

1569
01:26:42,250 --> 01:26:42,460
SHUT UP!

1570
01:26:42,670 --> 01:26:44,840
HE'S GONNA DROWN,
AND HE DOESN'T EVEN CARE.

1571
01:26:45,050 --> 01:26:46,510
DO IT.
NO.

1572
01:26:46,720 --> 01:26:48,970
DO IT!

1573
01:27:31,930 --> 01:27:34,260
[THUNDER]

1574
01:27:41,480 --> 01:27:43,860
THAT'S ENOUGH.

1575
01:28:13,510 --> 01:28:15,850
[GAGGING]

1576
01:29:33,340 --> 01:29:35,630
[CRASH]

1577
01:30:02,410 --> 01:30:04,620
OH.

1578
01:30:05,830 --> 01:30:08,040
OH.

1579
01:31:53,520 --> 01:31:56,320
Christof:
I WANT TO TALK TO HIM.

1580
01:32:14,670 --> 01:32:15,460
TRUMAN.

1581
01:32:15,670 --> 01:32:16,460
[GASPS]

1582
01:32:16,670 --> 01:32:19,090
YOU CAN SPEAK.

1583
01:32:19,800 --> 01:32:22,550
[OVER SPEAKER]
I CAN HEAR YOU.

1584
01:32:26,600 --> 01:32:27,180
WHO ARE YOU?

1585
01:32:27,390 --> 01:32:29,390
